HEADWORD: Shopman
<hw>Shop"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Shopmen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A shopkeeper;
a retailer.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who serves in a shop; a salesman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One who works in a shop or a factory.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shopper</ent>⟦br⟧
